    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Wood from Picea mariana, found in North America. It is a yellow, lightweight wood with a straight grain logged primarily as pulp wood, but also used for piles, posts, and ship construction.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
